        <section class="inner reasons clear">
                <h2 class="blue-bg">A NEW ZEALAND SKI RESORT FOR EVERYONE</h2>

                <div class="carousel-left">Previous</div>
                <div class="carousel">
                    <div class="carousel-container">

                        
                            <div class="carousel-item current">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Sth Island&#039;s Largest Ski Area">Sth Island&#039;s Largest Ski Area</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Snow-Sports-School-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-TREBLE-CONE-SKIING-1.jpg" alt="Skiing a groomed run at Treble Cone overlooking Lake Wanaka" />
                            <p class="text"><p><span>Over four remarkable basins (550ha), Treble Cone is the l</span>argest ski area in Queenstown and Wanaka, <span>offing a massive diversity of terrain.</span> Undeniably something for everyone.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Longest Vertical Rise">Longest Vertical Rise</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Freeriding-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-11-2ski.JPG" alt="skiing some beautiful groomed runs at Treble Cone ski resort NZ" />
                            <p class="text"><p>Treble Cone is home to the longest ski and snowboard runs in the Queenstown and Wanaka lakes district. Treble Cone’s longest run is a leg burning 4km, with a vertical drop of 700m.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Legendary Off-Piste Terrain">Legendary Off-Piste Terrain</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Freeriding-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-TREBLE-CONE-SKIING-2.jpg" alt="Powder skiing at Treble Cone ski field NZ" />
                            <p class="text"><p>Challenge your turns in some of the most revered New Zealand snowboard and ski terrain. Complete with gullies, chutes, bowls and drops, whatever your off-piste taste, you will find your fix here.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Uncrowded Groomed Runs">Uncrowded Groomed Runs</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Snow-Sports-School-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-Instructor-and-students-skiing-groom.JPG" alt="Skiing groomed runs at Treble Cone with view over Lake Wanaka" />
                            <p class="text"><p>Master your turns or give the legs a deserved rest. Treble Cone is a New Zealand ski resort that gives you the space to do what you like, and what better place than a perfect, long groom.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Free Beginner Ski Lift">Free Beginner Ski Lift</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Snow-Sports-School-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-Beginner-snowboard-lesson.JPG" alt="Learning to Snowboard on Treble Cone&#039;s Free Beginner Lifts" />
                            <p class="text"><p>To encourage more beginners into our wonderful winter world, Treble Cone provides FREE lift access to the ‘Nice n’ Easy’ surface lift, located alongside the comforts of the Base Lodge and Café. </p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Skiing Queenstown &amp; Wanaka">Skiing Queenstown &amp; Wanaka</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Kids-and-Family-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-Family-on-base-deck.JPG" alt="Ski Family drinking coffee on Treble Cone NZ deck" />
                            <p class="text"><p>Queenstown and Wanaka are the epicenters of snow in the Southern Hemispher, famious for their proximity to four major ski resorts, alpine views and aprea ski.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Stunning View of Lake Wanaka">Stunning View of Lake Wanaka</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Freeriding-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-TREBLE-CONE-SKIING-3.jpg" alt="Powder day with a magic view over Lake Wanaka NZ" />
                            <p class="text"><p>Conquering the mountain or sipping coffee on the deck. There is no escaping the views over the majestic Lake Wanaka and jagged snow covered Southern Alps. Truly NZ’s best ski resort view.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Fantastic NZ Ski Holiday">Fantastic NZ Ski Holiday</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Snow-Sports-School-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-Instructor-Towing-Kids.JPG" alt="Instructor towing 2 kids across Treble Cone NZ" />
                            <p class="text"><p><span>Stay in the magic Wanaka (or Queenstown) and ride Treble Cone. Save on multi-day lift passes, rentals and lessons. On and off snow, this is a real <a href="/ski-new-zealand/your-guide-to-shred/">New Zealand ski</a> holiday.</span></p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Ski from Queenstown ">Ski from Queenstown </h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/_resampled/croppedimage14598-TCw201109.JPG" alt="TCw201109" />
                            <p class="text"><p>Located only 90 mins from Queenstown, the drive is half the adventure. See Queenstown from new heights (Crown Ranges) and cruise the shores of Lake Wanaka. Daily shuttles available. </p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                            <div class="carousel-item">                        
                            <h3 class="grey extra-bold" title="Closest Ski Field to Wanaka">Closest Ski Field to Wanaka</h3>

                            <img src="/assets/Uploads/Wanaka-Images/_resampled/croppedimage14598-TREBLE-CONE-076.jpg" alt="Looking over Lake Wanaka at Treble Cone ski field" />
                            <p class="text"><p>New Zealand’s closest ski field from the beautiful ski town of Wanaka. Located a scenic 35 minute drive along Lake Wanaka. Daily shuttles available from both Wanaka and Queenstown.</p></p>
                        </div>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
